<br>
I saw an interview with Rumsfield today, and the reporter asked him &quot;So you told Syria that military action was still a possibility&quot; Rumsfield responded with &quot;I don't think I've ever said that&quot; where as in cases like Iraq and North Korea they always added on to the end of a statement &quot;military action is still on the table&quot; so who knows.<br>
<br>
Honestly I dunno what the deal with Syria is because I've yet to do any research on it and they haven't been in the spot light. If the US plans on invading them, they better have some concrete evidence because unlike Iraq, Syria hasn't attacked anybody recently.<br>
<br>
What I would like to say though is regardless of what happens in Syria, we better handle the fuckin Israel/Palestine situation BEFORE we deal with Syria because the arab view of the United States is at an all time low and going into a second invasion without ending the palestine conflict will be the nail in the coffin in the eyes of many arab nations and how they view the U.S.<br>
