If the US would help the people who needed it the most first, and worry about the rest later, instead of helping those who can immediatly help them first, and worry about the rest later, wed have a lot less anti-Americanism to deal with. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fogelxanedu>Fogel Xanedu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Training Karnors</span><br>  Posts: 1365<br> <font color=#628CBC>(4/15/03 10:32:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=558.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Syria</span><hr size=1> If we helped people on a need by need basis, we'd have alot of people to help. I'm all for helping people but how long do you expect a country to continually shell out money, man power, and in alot of cases, soldiers lives without one bit of payback before you say enough is enough.<br>
<br>
